Chuck E. Cheese’s Plans to Expand Into Mexico, Reforma Reports

-- B y   A d r i a n a   L o p e z   C a r a v e o
-- 
2011-08-03T15:42:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-03/chuck-e-cheese-s-plans-to-expand-into-mexico-reforma-reports.html
CEC Entertainment Inc. (CEC) , operator of
Chuck E. Cheese’s family restaurants, has its first location in
 Mexico  under development, Reforma newspaper  reported  without
saying how it obtained the information.  The restaurant will likely be located in Monterrey, a city
in the northern state of Nuevo Leon, the Mexico City-based
newspaper said.  Chuck E. Cheese’s plans to open 10 restaurants in Mexico in
the next five years, according to the newspaper. The restaurants
offer pizza, games and prizes aimed at children. The company
owns about 500 locations, almost all in the U.S. and Canada.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Adriana Lopez Caraveo in Mexico City at 
 adrianalopez@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Goodman at 
 jgoodman19@bloomberg.net  